HEADWORD: Bubo
<hw>Bu"bo</hw> <pr>(b⟦umac⟧"b⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Buboes</plw> <pr>(-b⟦osl⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>bubo</ets> the groin, a swelling in the groin, Gr.
<grk>boubw`n</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An inflammation, with
enlargement, of a lymphatic gland, esp. in the groin, as in
syphilis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

